definitions.definition: A single- reed instrument musical instrument of the woodwind family, usually made of brass and with a distinctive loop bringing the bell upwards.
examples: I played the saxophone in high school.

definitions.definition: Someone who plays the saxophone; a saxophonist .
examples: The saxophones typically sit behind the flutes in a concert band.
